text: Discovery Kids was a Southeast Asian pay television channel owned by Warner Bros. Discovery EMEA. It launched on 2 April 2012. However, it was replaced by Discovery Family on 1 April 2016. ==History== Discovery Kids launched in Southeast Asia on 2 April 2012 as the first feed of Discovery Kids outside of Latin America after 2 years. On 15 February 2016, Doki premiered on Southeast Asian television on Discovery Kids. On April 1, 2016, Discovery Kids was replaced by Discovery Family. Category:Television channels in Asia
title: Discovery Kids (Southeast Asian TV channel)
